# COMMAND LINE: cpptraj $WORK/setup/4IRY_IS.prmtop 4IRY_cpptraj_rmsf.in
# Note: the input pdb file must be present in the directory where cpptraj is run (directory containing mdcrd files).
# This code first strips water molecules from the topology file.
# Then uses the topolgy file to calculate the RMSD per residue of the given structure.
#
parmstrip :WAT
reference 4IRY_I.pdb [inpcrd]
trajin 4IRY_image.mdcrd 1 last 1
#strip :Na+,Cl-

rmsd ref [inpcrd] out 4IRY_rmsd_ref_inpcrd.txt @CA
rmsd ref [inpcrd] perres perresavg 4IRY_rmsf_ref_inpcrd.txt perresmask @CA  perresinvert

#rmsd ref [inpcrd] perres perresavg 4IRY_rmsfcentered_ref_inpcrd.txt perresmask @CA  perrescenter perresinvert
# ATTN: centering (the above line) does not matter when only one atoms (CA as in here) is used for rmsf calculation.
#radgyr @CA out 4IRY_radgyr.txt
#average 4IRY_avg_equil.pdb pdb
#reference 4IRY_avg_equil.pdb [avg]
#rmsd ref [avg] perres perresout 4IRY_perres_fluc_ref_avg.txt @CA